    "body": "I'm a bit ambivalent about going to 64 bit ints for the node id. I think it is a good temporary workaround for the wrap-around problem, but as you do want to handle wrapping, it seems a double measure. At the least please add a regression test for the wrapping code, as with 64 bits is so unlikely to ever trigger that the code will rot.\r\n",
